# Rule: README.md

The repo-root `README.md` is **a pointer, not a document**. It must:

- link to `AGENTS.md` as the first thing an agent reads;
- list the current component / phase status (which packages exist, which
  components are shipped — read from `SPEC.md` when it exists);
- link to LICENSE.

It must **not**:

- duplicate content from `AGENTS.md`;
- include design details, FR/NFR lists, or ADRs;
- exceed 80 lines.

## Template (frontmatter is none — root README has no frontmatter)

```markdown
# <Project name>

<one paragraph: what it is, why it exists>

## Start here

- `<pointer 1>` — <why read it>
- `<pointer 2>` — <why read it>
- …

## Status

| Item | State |
|------|-------|
| <row> | <state> |
| … |  |

## License

<one line, link to LICENSE>.
```